cyclone.name: FRED
cyclone.current_location: about 150 miles WNW of Havana, Cuba
cyclone.trajectory: Moving northwest across the southeastern, central and northern Gulf of Mexico, expected to turn north and come ashore along the northern Gulf Coast then track inland through the Southeast U.S.

weather_observation.watch_coast: No tropical watches posted for the Mid-Atlantic coast
weather_observation.warning_coast: None in effect north of the Florida Panhandle
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Northern Gulf Coast from Mississippi to the central Florida Panhandle
weather_observation.closest_wind_data_location: Not available (Wilmington, DE not listed in wind-probability table)
weather_observation.wind: No tropical-storm-force winds expected; only occasional gusts below gale-force mid-week.
weather_observation.storm_surge: None expected along the Delaware coast.
weather_observation.rainfall: Remnant moisture may bring 1–2 inches of rain to the Delaware Valley mid-week, but widespread heavy totals are not anticipated.
